***************************************/
//Grease
@61000 = ~Wand of Grease~
@61001 = ~When activated, the wand will create a slippery layer of a fatty, greasy nature to cover a material surface. Any creature entering the area or caught in it when the spell is cast must save or slip and slide, unable to move effectively. Those who successfully save can move, albeit slowly, for the rest of the round (but will need to save vs. Wand again the following round). Those who remain in the area are allowed a Saving Throw each round until they escape the area.

STATISTICS:
(Conjuration/Summoning)

Charge abilities:
– Grease
  – Covers a surface with a slippery layer
  – Any creature within the area must save or slip and slide, each round
  – Saving creatures can move slowly for the rest of the round
  Range: 30 ft.
  Duration: %duration%
  Area of Effect: 15-ft. radius
  Saving Throw: Save vs. Wand at +2

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~

//Armor
@61002 = ~Wand of Armor~
@61003 = ~When activated, the wand generates a magical field of force that serves as if it were scale mail armor. This does not hinder movement, adds no weight or encumbrance, and doesn't prevent spellcasting.

STATISTICS:
(Conjuration)

Charge abilities:
– Armor
  – Applies a field of magical force of armor around the wielder (AC 6).
  – Does not affect spellcasting or thieving skills
  Duration: 9 hours
  Area of Effect: Self
  Saving Throw: None

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Burning Hands
@61004 = ~Wand of Burning Hands~
@61005 = ~When activated, a jet of searing flame shoots forward in a horizontal arc of about 120 degrees, with a 5 ft. length. Any creature in the area of the flames suffers 1d3 +%magnitude%  points of fire damage. Those successfully saving vs. Wand receive half damage.

STATISTICS:
(Alteration)

Charge abilities:
– Burning Hands
  – Creates a fan-line cone of fire 5 ft. from the wielder
  Damage: 1d3 +%magnitude% points of fire damage
  Duration: Instant
  Area of Effect: 5-ft. cone with 120-deg. arc
  Saving Throw: Save vs. Wand for 1/2 damage

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Charm Person
@61006 = ~Wand of Charm Person~
@61007 = ~This wand will charm its humanoid† target when activated; the charmed individual may be given orders, and they will carry them out as quickly as possible. They will also gladly provide valuable information to their new ally.

If the caster harms, or attempts to harm, the charmed person by some overt action, or if Dispel Magic is successfully cast upon the charmed person, the charm spell is broken. If two or more charm effects simultaneously affect a creature, the most recent charm takes precedence. Note that the subject has full memory of the events that took place while <PRO_HESHE> was charmed. Also note that you cannot have a charmed creature leave the area where <PRO_HESHE> was charmed.

†: Humanoids are any bipedal human, demihuman, or humanoid of man-size or smaller, such as brownies, dryads, dwarves, elves, gnolls, gnomes, goblins, half-elves, halflings, half-orcs, hobgoblins, humans, kobolds, lizard men, nixies, orcs, pixies, sprites, troglodytes, and others. Thus, a 10th-level fighter could be charmed, but an ogre could not.

STATISTICS:
(Enchantment/Charm)

Charge abilities:
– Charm Person
  – Charms the target to be ordered or spoken to
  Range: Visual range
  Duration: 5 rounds
  Area of Effect: 1 person
  Saving Throw: Save vs. Wand (at +3) negates

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Color Spray
@61008 = ~Wand of Color Spray~
@61009 = ~This wand will project a vivid, fan-shaped spray of clashing colors to spring forth from itself, causing 1d6 creatures within the area to be affected in order of increasing distance. All creatures affected that have 4 Hit Dice or less must make a successful Saving Throw or be rendered unconscious for 5 rounds.

STATISTICS:
(Alteration)

