//Sanctuary
@61514 = ~Wand of Sanctuary~
@61515 = ~This wand causes all of the wielder's opponents to ignore <PRO_HISHER> existence as if <PRO_HESHE> were invisible. While protected by this spell, the subject cannot take direct offensive action without breaking the spell, but may use non-attack spells or otherwise act in any way that does not violate the prohibition against offensive action. This allows a warded person to heal wounds, for example, or to Bless <PRO_HIMHER>self. The wielder cannot cast spells on other creatures without ending the spell.

STATISTICS:
(Abjuration)

Charge abilities:
– Sanctuary
  – Ignored as if invisible
  – Can move, use thief skills, and heal/buff self
  Duration: %duration%
  Area of Effect: Self
  Saving Throw: None

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Shillelagh
@61516 = ~Wand of Shillelagh~
@61517 = ~When activated, this wand creates a magical cudgel that has a +1 bonus to its attack roll and inflicts 2d4 points of damage on opponents.

STATISTICS:
(Alteration)

Charge abilities:
– Shillelagh
  – Creates weightless magical club
    – Deals 2d4 crushing damage
    – +1 bonus to THAC0
  Duration: %duration%
  Area of Effect: Self
  Saving Throw: None

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Armor of Faith
@61518 = ~Wand of Armor of Faith~
@61519 = ~When activated, the wielder receives significant protection against melee, ranged, and magical attacks. This magical armor is a force of energy that absorbs %magnitude%% of the damage intended for the wielder.

STATISTICS:
(Abjuration)

Charge abilities:
– Armor of Faith
  – Absorbs %magnitude%% of incoming damage
  Duration: %duration%
  Area of Effect: Self
  Saving Throw: None

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Doom
@61520 = ~Wand of Doom~
@61521 = ~When activated, this wand causes a feeling of doom to overwhelm the target. For the duration of the spell, the target receives a -2 penalty to <PRO_HISHER> THAC0 and Saving Throws. There is no Saving Throw for this spell.

STATISTICS:
(Alteration)

Charge abilities:
– Doom
  – -2 penalty to THAC0
  – -2 penalty to saving throws
  Range: 25 ft.
  Duration: 1 turn
  Area of Effect: 1 creature
  Saving Throw: None

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Faerie Fire
@61522 = ~Wand of Faerie Fire~
@61523 = ~Upon uttering the activation phrase, this wand outlines one or more creatures with a pale violet glow, making positions and movements easily visible. Outlined creatures are easier to strike, giving them an Armor Class penalty of -2.

STATISTICS:
(Alteration)

Charge abilities:
– Faerie Fire
  – Purple flame outline
  – -2 penalty to Armor Class
  Range: Sight
  Duration: %duration%
  Area of Effect: 10-ft. radius
  Saving Throw: None

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Spirit Ward
@61524 = ~Wand of Spirit Ward~
@61525 = ~Upon activation, the recipient is surrounded with a magical barrier at a distance of one foot. Spirits, fey creatures, elementals, and spectral undead receive a penalty of -2 to hit when attacking the protected creature. In addition, the recipient gains a +3 bonus to Saving Throws against all spells that belong to the Enchantment school. This spell cannot be cast on spirits, fey creatures, elementals, or spectral undead.

STATISTICS:
(Abjuration)

Charge abilities:
– Spirit Ward
  – Spirits, fey creatures, elementals, and spectral undead
    – -2 penalty to THAC0 to attack recipient
  – +3 bonus to Saving Throws against Enchantment spells
  Range: Touch
  Duration: %duration%
  Area of Effect: 1 creature
  Saving Throw: None

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


/***************************************
